{{Infobox book| <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = ''Thou Art That: Transforming Religious Metaphor'' | title_orig = | translator = | image = Thou Art That (book).png | caption = | author = [[Joseph Campbell]] | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = [[Collected Works of Joseph Campbell]] | subject = [[Religion]]/[[Religion and Mythology|Comparative Mythology]] | publisher = [[New World Library]] | release_date = 2001-10-10 | media_type = Print | pages = 192 | isbn = 1-57731-202-3 | dewey = 230 21 | congress = BR115.L25 C36 2001 | oclc= 46969766 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Thou Art That''''' is a book by [[Joseph Campbell]] exploring the [[mythological]] underpinnings of the [[Judeo-Christian]] tradition. It was edited posthumously from Campbell's lectures and unpublished writing by [[Eugene Kennedy]].
Published by [[New World Library]] in 2001, ''Thou Art That'' was the first title in the [[Joseph Campbell Foundation]]'s ''[[Collected Works of Joseph Campbell]]'' series.
